  "response_text": "In a bright, minimalist laundry-room set, two women stand behind a counter with two white top-loading washing machines angled toward each other in the center. A red-and-purple box of Wisk Tablets sits on the left side of the counter, beside a folded white garment, while a green-and-yellow box of another laundry product sits on the right. Overhead, large round recessed lights glow against pale walls, giving the space a clean, studio-like look. The woman on the left has long light-brown hair and wears a pale lavender V-neck sweater and light pants; she stands with one hand on her hip, watching. The woman on the right has short blonde hair and wears a light blue short-sleeved button-up shirt; she holds up a white shirt marked with a yellowish stain, then lowers it toward the washer on her side.\n\nThe woman in lavender looks unimpressed but attentive. She reaches down to her own pile of laundry, lifts a white shirt, and holds it up in front of her. The shirt has obvious food-like stains: a green streak down one side and orange-brown blotches on the other. As she displays the stained shirt, small white text appears along the bottom listing the featured stains as “ketchup, green beans, steak sauce.” She turns the shirt slightly so the stains face outward, then lowers it, looking down as if placing it into the washer.\n\nThe blonde woman on the right stands with one hand on her hip, then picks up a small green measuring scoop. She extends it over her washing machine and pours a stream of green powder down into the open washer. The woman in lavender, on the left, then raises two small white tablet-like detergent pieces, one in each hand, holding them near her shoulders to show their compact round shape. In the wider view, the Wisk Tablets box remains clearly visible on the left side of the counter while the other product’s box remains on the right.\n\nThe woman in lavender turns back to her washer and reaches inside. Instead of pulling out an ordinary stained garment, she lifts a large square of thick, bright green grass, like a slab of turf. Small text at the lower left reads “Dramatization.” She raises the turf higher with both hands, its dense blades facing forward and a darker underside visible along the bottom edge, presenting it almost like an exaggerated “grass stain.” She looks directly ahead while holding the grassy square up in front of her chest. The blonde woman glances over from the right, still holding the green scoop, her posture suggesting surprise or curiosity. The woman in lavender then no longer has the turf in her hands and lifts both empty palms in front of her, as if to show the demonstration is complete.\n\nThe commercial ends with a product display on a warm-toned countertop. At left is a neatly folded stack of white laundry. To the right of the stack are two red Wisk Tablets packages: a taller upright box and a rectangular box lying lengthwise. Both packages feature the large yellow-orange “Wisk” name and the words “Tablets,” with white tablet graphics splashing through blue water imagery. Along the bottom, small white text reads: “Demonstration on non-bleach tablets only. Bleach tablets coming soon.”",
